The point is to introduce three methods more in ParallelComputer:
public static Computer methods(ExecucionService e)
public static Computer classes(ExecucionService e)
public static Computer classesAndMethods(ExecucionService e)

If the parallelism in the surefire is enabled, these method are called. The number of Threads are defined via Executor by user/surefire.

The point is to introduce three methods in JUnit class ParallelComputer
which can be called by any user like maven-surefire or maven surefire providers.


public static Computer methods(ExecucionService e)

public static Computer classes(ExecucionService e)

public static Computer classesAndMethods(ExecucionService e)


The Executor is constructed by the user/surefire with any number of Threads in the pool, like num of CPU cores, infinitive, etc.

The parallelism in surefire still has some issues. So the best is to use this facility.

When only @ExcludeCategory is used on the suite and test case has a test without Category annotation, this test is executed.

It should not, which is mentioned in Categories Javadoc having sample code -only @Test should fail.

See our internal test:

CategoryTest#testCountOnAWithoutSlowTests()

There the test noCategory() should not be running. Thus getRunCount should return 1.

Result result = JUnitCore.runClasses(SomeAreSlowSuite.class);
assertEquals(2, result.getRunCount());

